cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models, specifically a long short-term memory (LSTM) neural network, to model quantum experiments. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of these models for automated design of experiments also involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the generation of large datasets, which could fall under the category of statistical learning (cs.SD).
